SPARK – Live Circuit UI Spec  
(Everything is a schematic that jitters, breathes, and breaks)

--------------------------------------------------
1. COLOR TOKENS (Tailwind plugin)
--------------------------------------------------
--void: #050505;  
--matrix: #00FF41;  
--alert: #E30000;  
--proc: #FFD400;  
--glow-matrix: 0 0 4px var(--matrix), 0 0 8px var(--matrix);  
--glow-alert: 0 0 4px var(--alert), 0 0 8px var(--alert);  
--crt-mask: linear-gradient(transparent 50%, rgba(255,255,255,.03) 50%);  
--scanline: repeating-linear-gradient(0deg, rgba(0,255,65,.06) 0 1px, transparent 1px 2px);

--------------------------------------------------
2. GLOBAL BASE (add to globals.css)
--------------------------------------------------
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;700&display=swap');

@layer base {
  body {
    @apply bg-[var(--void)] text-[var(--matrix)] font-mono text-[10px] leading-[10px] antialiased;
  }
  *::selection { background: var(--matrix); color: var(--void); }
}

@layer utilities {
  .crt::before {
    content: '';
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    background: var(--scanline);
    background-size: 100% 2px;
    mix-blend-mode: screen;
    pointer-events: none;
    animation: scan 250ms linear infinite;
  }
  @keyframes scan { to { transform: translateY(2px); } }
}

--------------------------------------------------
3. THE “WIRE” COMPONENT (SVG inside a div)
--------------------------------------------------
<div className="wire-wrapper" data-state={state}>  {/* idle | success | fail | proc */}
  <svg className="w-full h-full">
    <path className="wire-bg" />   {/* matte track */}
    <path className="wire-core" /> {/* animated stroke */}
  </svg>
</div>

--------------------------------------------------
4. TAILWIND CLASSES
--------------------------------------------------
.wire-wrapper         @apply relative w-full h-4 overflow-hidden;
.wire-bg               @apply stroke-gray-800 stroke-[2];
.wire-core             @apply fill-none stroke-[3] stroke-[var(--matrix)];
.wire-core.success      @apply stroke-[var(--matrix)] drop-shadow-[var(--glow-matrix)];
.wire-core.fail        @apply stroke-[var(--alert)] drop-shadow-[var(--glow-alert)];
.wire-core.proc        @apply stroke-[var(--proc)] drop-shadow-[var(--glow-proc)];

--------------------------------------------------
5. FRAMER MOTION STATES (React, but portable)
--------------------------------------------------
const states = {
  idle:    { pathLength: 1, opacity: 0.4, stroke: '#00FF41', filter: '' },
  success: { pathLength: 1, opacity: 1, stroke: '#00FF41', filter: 'drop-shadow(0 0 4px #00FF41)' },
  fail:    { pathLength: 0.6, opacity: [1,0,1,0,1], stroke: '#E30000', filter: 'drop-shadow(0 0 6px #E30000)' },
  proc:    { pathLength: [0,1], opacity: 1, stroke: '#FFD400', filter: 'drop-shadow(0 0 6px #FFD400)' }
};

<motion.path
  d={pathData}
  className="wire-core"
  initial="idle"
  animate={state}          // one of the keys above
  variants={states}
  transition={{
    pathLength: { type: 'spring', stiffness: 400, damping: 20 },
    opacity: { repeat: state==='fail' ? Infinity : 0, duration: .18 }
  }}
/>

--------------------------------------------------
6. JITTER & CURSOR FX (pure CSS)
--------------------------------------------------
.blink { animation: blink 1.1 steps(2) infinite; }
@keyframes blink { 50% { opacity: 0; } }

.jitter {
  animation: jitter .18s steps(2) infinite;
  text-shadow: 0 0 1px var(--matrix), 0 0 3px var(--matrix);
}
@keyframes jitter {
  0%   { transform: translate(0, 0); }
  25%  { transform: translate(-.5px, .5px); }
  50%  { transform: translate(.5px, -.5px); }
  75%  { transform: translate(-.5px, -.5px); }
  100% { transform: translate(0, 0); }
}

--------------------------------------------------
7. USAGE SNIPPET
--------------------------------------------------
<main className="crt min-h-screen p-4 grid gap-2">
  <div className="text-[8px] uppercase jitter">// LIVE CIRCUIT v1.0</div>
  <Wire state={status} />
</main>

--------------------------------------------------
8. NOTES
--------------------------------------------------
- Keep SVG paths single-segment so pathLength animates smoothly.  
- Use `stroke-linecap: round` for industrial-plug look.  
- For branching circuits, wrap each segment in its own Wire component; cascade state changes with a slight stagger (Framer’s `delayChildren`).  
- When a node fires, trigger a tiny `useSound` tick and a 20ms screen shake (`motion.div` with `x:[0,1,0]`).

